        <headline>Flood Advisory issued August 2 at 9:26PM MDT until August 3 at 12:45AM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Small stream flooding caused by excessive rainfall is
expected.

* WHERE...A portion of northeast Montana, including the following
counties, Daniels and Sheridan.

* WHEN...Until 1245 AM MDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Rises in small streams and normally dry stream beds. Some
low-water crossings may become impassable.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 925 PM MDT, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges
indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. This will cause
small stream flooding. Between 1 and 3 inches of rain have
fallen.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Scobey, Flaxville, Madoc, Whitetail, Port Of Scobey,
Redstone, Archer, Navajo, Daleview and Four Buttes.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the
dangers of flooding.</instruction>
